<br>
<!--EZCODE AUTOLINK START--><a href="http://www.dfas.mil/money/milpay/pay/2003paytable.pdf">www.dfas.mil/money/milpay...ytable.pdf</a><!--EZCODE AUTOLINK END--><br>
<br>
An E-1 will make about $1200/mo, plus another $250/mo for housing ($450 if married or with a kid).<br>
<br>
It does rise pretty notably, though, with promotion and years of experience.  An E-5 with 6 years' experience will be making about 24k/year, and an E-9 with 10 years' experience will be making over 40k.<br>
<br>
That said, add on top of this a lot of side benefits, and the pay isn't quite the welfare-poverty-level it sounds like; but by no means is it good.  Officer pay is quite a bit better; starting pay is in the mid-20's, but rises pretty quickly into the 40s+, with the same benefits and BAH on top.<br>
<br>
An O-7 or higher can break 100k/year before any of the benefits are added in.. but that's higher than 99.9% of people would reach, I would imagine. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#4D4D4D><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub101.ezboard.com/bthetribunaldotorg.showUserPublicProfile?gid=caledhontelrana>Caledhon TelRana</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>I read boards more<br>than I play EQ....</span><br>  Posts: 1066<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(4/17/03 11:59:48 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub101.ezboard.com/fthetribunaldotorgfrm36.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=625.topic&index=46>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: US War Crimes?</span><hr size=1> O-7 is Brigadier General.  So, yeah... not just a whole ton of those around. <p><!--EZCODE IMAGE START--><img src="http://www.visveres.myguilds.com/sigs/caledhon.gif" style="border:0;"/><!--EZCODE IMAGE END--></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#333333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub101.ezboard.com/bthetribunaldotorg.showUserPublicProfile?gid=wenin>Wenin</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>I read porn more<BR>
